javax.json

Class JsonArrayBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.json.JsonArrayBuilder

  • public class JsonArrayBuilder
extends Object
    Builds a JsonArray from scratch. It uses builder pattern to build the array model and the builder methods can be chained while building the JSON array.

    For example, for the following JSON array 

     
 [
     { "type": "home", "number": "212 555-1234" },
     { "type": "fax", "number": "646 555-4567" }
 ]
    a JsonArray instance can be built using: 

     
 JsonArray value = new JsonArrayBuilder()
     .add(new JsonObjectBuilder()
         .add("type", "home")
         .add("number", "212 555-1234"))
     .add(new JsonObjectBuilder()
         .add("type", "fax")
         .add("number", "646 555-4567"))
     .build();
    See Also:
    JsonObjectBuilder
